titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Chief Judge Morrison C. England, Jr on 9/22/14 GRANTING 25 Motion to Sever and Change Venue. Surewest Telephone and Surewest Televideo are hereby SEVERED and this case is TRANSFERRED to the Central District of Illinois as to defendants Surewest Telephone and Surewest Televideo only. Sprint Communications shall remain the plaintiff and Verizon California, Inc. and Pacific Bell Telephone Company shall remain the defendants in this action in this court. (Manzer, C)

titleInfo.title: Sprint Communications Company L.P. v. Pacific Bell Telephone Company et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Chief Judge Morrison C. England, Jr. on 10/14/2014. (1) Plaintiff Sprint Communications Company L.P.' s claims against defendant Verizon California Inc. are hereby SEVERED pursuant to Fed. R. Civ. P. 21. It is further ORDERED this case is hereby TRANSFERRED to the United StatesDistrict Court for the Eastern District of Missouri, Eastern Division, as to Defendant Verizon California Inc. only. Clerk is DIRECTED to take all steps necessary to effectuate this transfer. After transfer of defendant Verizon California Inc. as set forth above. Sprint Communications Company L.P. SHALL REMAIN the plaintiff and Pacific Bell Telephone Company, doing business as AT&T California, SHALL REMAIN the defendant in action in United States District Court for the Eastern District of California. (Marciel, M)
